<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Camden County Property Research | Makeaway</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Research notes for a Camden County, Georgia A-F zoned property being evaluated for a family compound and homestead."
    />
  </head>

  <body>
    <main>
      <a class="back-link" href="/">← Back to home</a>

      <section class="hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Makeaway Research</p>
        <h1>Camden County Property Research</h1>
        <p class="intro">
          Notes, links, and open questions for evaluating a rural Camden County,
          Georgia property as a possible family compound and homestead.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="summary-grid">
        <article class="summary-card">
          <span class="label">Location</span>
          <strong>Camden County, Georgia</strong>
          <p>Near White Oak / Owens Ferry Road area.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="summary-card">
          <span class="label">Parcel ID</span>
          <strong>039 004</strong>
          <p>Identified from the Camden County zoning lookup map.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="summary-card">
          <span class="label">Zoning / Land Use</span>
          <strong>A-F</strong>
          <p>Agriculture Forestry.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="summary-card">
          <span class="label">Coordinates</span>
          <strong>30.987852, -81.801919</strong>
          <p>Coordinates used to locate the tract on the zoning map.</p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Goal</h2>
        <p>
          The goal is to determine whether this property could support a
          multi-home family compound, homestead, or rural retreat while staying
          compliant with Camden County zoning, septic, well, access, and building
          requirements.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>What I’ve Found So Far</h2>

        <div class="finding-list">
          <article class="finding">
            <h3>The parcel appears to be A-F Agriculture Forestry.</h3>
            <p>
              The Camden County zoning lookup showed Parcel ID <strong>039 004</strong>
              with Land Use Code <strong>A-F</strong> and Land Use Description
              <strong>Agriculture Forestry</strong>.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="finding">
            <h3>A-F zoning may be favorable for a family compound.</h3>
            <p>
              The county code needs to be confirmed directly with Camden County,
              but A-F appears to be one of the zoning categories where rural
              residential, agricultural, and family-use dwelling options may be
              possible.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="finding">
            <h3>Septic and well feasibility may be the real limiting factor.</h3>
            <p>
              Even if zoning allows additional dwellings, each house may require
              Health Department approval for septic and well placement. Soil,
              upland acreage, wetlands, floodplain, and spacing requirements
              could limit the number of practical homesites.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="finding">
            <h3>Multiple homes need county confirmation.</h3>
            <p>
              The biggest question is whether multiple single-family dwellings
              can remain on one owner-occupied parcel, or whether Camden County
              would require subdivision, separate addresses, or another approval
              process.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Important Links</h2>

        <div class="link-grid">
          <a
            class="link-card"
            href="https://ccboc.maps.arcgis.com/apps/instant/lookup/index.html?appid=38333ef7a1d54dbc9a6fa0ac1610dd84"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            <span class="label">Map</span>
            <strong>Camden County Zoning Look-Up</strong>
            <p>Used to locate Parcel ID 039 004 and confirm A-F land use.</p>
          </a>

          <a
            class="link-card"
            href="https://www.camdencountyga.gov/1239/Ordinances-Codes#docaccess-d4cf997f699fcb89fac314f81b34ce36e60effb80fbc60320b7c85dad1dd8909"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            <span class="label">Code</span>
            <strong>Camden County Ordinances & Codes</strong>
            <p>County ordinances and development code documents.</p>
          </a>

          <a
            class="link-card"
            href="https://www.camdencountyga.gov/1246/Zoning"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            <span class="label">County</span>
            <strong>Camden County Zoning</strong>
            <p>Official county zoning information and related resources.</p>
          </a>

          <a
            class="link-card"
            href="https://www.camdencountyga.gov/74/Planning-Development"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            <span class="label">Contact</span>
            <strong>Planning & Development</strong>
            <p>Department to contact before relying on any interpretation.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Questions to Ask Camden County</h2>

        <div class="question-box">
          <p>
            I am considering purchasing Parcel ID <strong>039 004</strong>,
            located near Owens Ferry Road in Camden County, Georgia. The zoning
            lookup appears to show the property as <strong>A-F Agriculture Forestry</strong>.
          </p>

          <p>
            I would like to know whether this parcel can be used for an
            owner-occupied family compound or homestead with multiple
            single-family dwellings for family members.
          </p>

          <ol>
            <li>Can you confirm the exact zoning district for Parcel ID 039 004?</li>
            <li>Does A-F zoning allow multiple single-family dwellings on one owner-occupied parcel?</li>
            <li>If yes, how many dwellings could be allowed on approximately 25 acres?</li>
            <li>Would the additional dwellings require subdivision?</li>
            <li>Would each dwelling need its own septic system and well?</li>
            <li>Are modular homes, manufactured homes, barndominiums, or tiny homes allowed?</li>
            <li>Are there floodplain, wetland, or upland soil limitations on this parcel?</li>
            <li>Can RVs or campers be used temporarily during construction?</li>
            <li>Would separate addresses be available for family dwellings?</li>
            <li>What permits or pre-application meetings would be required?</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Due Diligence Checklist</h2>

        <div class="checklist">
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Confirm zoning with Camden County Planning</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Confirm whether multiple dwellings are allowed</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Ask if subdivision is required</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Request parcel survey or plat</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Review deed restrictions and easements</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Check wetlands and floodplain</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Verify soil suitability for septic</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Confirm well requirements and spacing</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Confirm driveway / road access requirements</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Confirm power provider and utility access</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Ask about livestock, gardens, and agricultural use</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" /> Estimate cost for land clearing, driveway, well, septic, and power</label>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section warning">
        <h2>Important Note</h2>
        <p>
          This page is a research notebook, not legal, zoning, engineering, or
          permitting advice. Before making an offer, the intended use should be
          confirmed directly with Camden County Planning & Development, the
          Camden County Health Department, a surveyor, and a real estate attorney
          or closing professional.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

